Admissions Forms









Application Forms




Change of Campus



You may request a change of campus by completing this form. One of our admissions counselors will follow up with you once your request has been completed. For additional information, questions or concerns please email pdcadmissions@csusb.edu.
Change of Campus Form





Change of Major For New Students (Fall 23 Only)



As of Monday, August 22, 2022 any new student who has accepted their offer will need to submit the form through their MyCoyote. You may use the following Change of Major instructions for assistance.
If you have not received a decision or have yet to accept your offer. You may submit a request by calling (909)-537-5188.





Date of Birth Change



This form is for all applicants who would like to update/change their Date of Birth. This is most common for students who incorrectly reported their Date of Birth while applying to CSUSB. A correct Date of Birth is required for the activation of your myCoyote account.
*Documentation is required: State or Federally issued Identification or Birth Certificate may be submitted. Use the link to upload documents directly through your myCoyote log-in:
Ensure that your file is named with the document type, for example: Birth Certificate

Secure Document Upload
Date of Birth Change Form





Early Summer Starter Application (ESS)



The Early Summer Starter (ESS) Application is designed for incoming students to the Fall term who wish to get a head start on their courses and start at CSUSB in the Summer. The ESS Application is only available to students who have accepted their Fall offer of Admission and are not otherwise enrolled in courses for the summer term at any other institution. ESS applications will not be fully processed until Final Official transcripts are submitted and Fall admission has been finalized.
*Please note: Submitting an Early Summer Starter Application does not affect your Fall Admission decision in any way. Your ESS application will not be fully processed until your final transcripts have been received and your Fall admission has been cleared by the Office of Admission and Student Recruitment.
Early Summer Starter Application





Faculty/Staff/Dependents Fee Waiver



Members of the faculty and staff at Cal State San Bernardino and their dependents may be eligible to participate in a system-wide fee waiver program that allows for career and personal development offered through the CSUSB Human Resources Department. For details on your eligibility and the required forms, visit the Human Resources Department fee waiver page.
If you plan to enroll in courses at CSUSB for your own personal growth and you are not seeking any degree, complete and submit the Non-Degree Seeking/Transitory Student Application to the Office of Admissions and Student Recruitment in University Hall, Room 107 or fax (909) 537-7034.
Eligible individuals who wish to enroll in courses at CSUSB into a degree program must complete and submit a CSU application at Cal State Apply. Students must be eligible for admission to the university.





Legal Name Change



 This form is for incoming new CSUSB students who would like to change their "First, Middle, and Last Name" prior to course registration.
*Documentation is required: Birth Certificate, State or Federally issued Identification or Marriage License may be submitted.

Use the link to upload documents directly through your myCoyote log in:
Ensure that your file is named with the document type, example: Marriage License

Secure Document Upload
Please Note: All continuing students and incoming students who have already registered for courses you will need to submit a Name Change Request with the Office of Registrars.

Name Change Form





Non-Degree Seeking Student Application - Transitory Student



 The transitory application for CSUSB is available to students who are part of special programs allowing them to attend courses without being fully admitted to CSUSB. Transitory programs are for students who do not intend to graduate with a degree from CSUSB. There are several types of non-degree seeking/transitory programs at CSUSB so please be sure to check the box for your desired program.
Please visit Non-Degree programs for more information about out Transitory programs.
Transitory applications should be submitted through each program's coordinator. If you have additional questions, please email admissionsapps@csusb.edu.  

Non-Degree Seeking Student Application - Transitory Student (PDF)





Social Security Number Change



This form is for all applicants who would like to update/change their Social Security Number (SSN). This is most commonly done for students who incorrectly reported their SSN while applying to CSUSB.
*Documentation is required: Social Security Card may be submitted. Use the link to upload documents directly through your myCoyote log in:
Ensure that your file is named with the document type, example: SSN Card
​​​​​​
Secure Document Upload
Social Security Number Change Form





Student Data Changes



Students are able to manage many aspects of their Personal Information through their myCoyote account. In order to do this, please log onto your myCoyote account and navigate to the to Personal Information tile. Once there you can manage the following personal information items:

Home & Mailing Address
Preferred Name
Phone number
Personal email address
Emergency Contacts

Items that cannot be updated and that require submitting a form along with documentation include:

Legal Name
Social Security
Date of Birth
Major Change 






Western Undergraduate Exchange (WUE)



 The WICHE/WUE program allows out of state applicants from the participating western region to attend CSUSB and pay no more than 150% of resident tuition fees while retaining their home state residency status. Students must meet all admission requirements and be otherwise eligible for admission to CSUSB as well as submit the WICHE/WUE application directly to CSUSB.
Please visit Western Undergraduate Exchange program for more information about the WICHE/WUE program.

WICHE/WUE Application
